# Vitest test patterns

- Import test primitives from `vitest` (`describe`, `it`, `expect`). Never import from `@jest/globals`.
- Use `vi` for mocks and spies. Do not use `jest`.
- One `describe` block per exported symbol. Nest `describe` blocks for variants.
- Test names are imperative — "returns X when Y", not "should return X".
- For React components, use `@testing-library/react` and assert on accessible names with `getByRole`.
- For deterministic tests against time-relative output, pass an explicit `now` reference instead of relying on `Date.now()`.

## Example

```ts
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { picsumUrl } from "../picsum";

describe("picsumUrl", () => {
  it("returns a deterministic URL for a given seed", () => {
    expect(picsumUrl({ seed: "x", width: 100, height: 100 })).toBe(
      "https://picsum.photos/seed/x/100/100"
    );
  });

  it("URL-encodes seeds with special characters", () => {
    expect(picsumUrl({ seed: "spring campaign", width: 50, height: 50 })).toBe(
      "https://picsum.photos/seed/spring%20campaign/50/50"
    );
  });
});
```
